parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and High RPM Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling when put into reverse gear and high RPM can cause loss of control, accidents, and engine damage.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when shifted into reverse gear
the engine RPM is higher than normal
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty temperature gauge sending unit can cause inaccurate temperature readings, leading to engine overheating, damage, or failure.
symptoms: The temperature gauge is not accurate
the engine temperature is not displayed correctly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fan belt can cause engine overheating, damage, or failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: The fan belt is worn or broken
the cooling system is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty EGR temperature sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: the EGR system is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty oxygen sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: the oxygen sensor is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A leaking valve cover can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and decreased engine performance.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the valve cover

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause engine performance issues, such as decreased power, rough idling, and misfires, which can lead to reduced fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine damage.

The failure of fuel injectors can cause engine performance issues, such as decreased power, rough idling, and misfires, which can lead to reduced fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine damage.
The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration or deceleration, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to engage
the cruise control system fails to disengage
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates unpredictably
the cruise control light on the dashboard flashes or remains illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal position sensor can cause the brake lights to remain illuminated, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The brake lights remain illuminated even when the brake pedal is not pressed
the brake lights flicker or flash
the vehicle's anti-lock braking system (ABS) warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failure can cause loss of power, unexpected acceleration, or stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving on highways or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the vehicle stalls or loses power.
